comments.text:
It's all very sad. I'm so sorry. The game affected me very badly. Firstly, it seemed like the coach made a big mistake in choosing the lineup and tactics. Secondly, the players playing in defense looked very bad. It's a shame, especially losing by such a score in a derby is very hard for the fans. In my opinion, the defenders need to strengthen their physical play. In almost all episodes, the defenders were helpless in one-on-one battles.


Es muy triste. Lo siento mucho. El partido me afectó muchísimo. Primero, me pareció que el entrenador cometió un grave error al elegir la alineación y la táctica. Segundo, los jugadores de defensa se vieron muy mal. Es una pena, sobre todo perder por un marcador tan alto en un derbi es muy duro para la afición. En mi opinión, los defensas necesitan reforzar su juego físico. En casi todos los episodios, los defensas se mostraron indefensos en los duelos uno contra uno.

comments.author: @shubhamshufflenegi
comments.text:
Uff… the final two years of my GOAT Ronaldo and the other GOAT Messi. What will happen after 2027, when they retire? 😢
The excitement, the aura, the magnetic attraction that pulls us into every single match of theirs will vanish. Nothing will ever feel the same again. They light up every match they play even it's a friendly, the aura is enough.

I feel scared even imagining those days—no more debates, no fan fights in social media and everywhere in the streets or anywhere weather it's about Messi scoring twice today and Ronaldo responding with a brace the next day… no more “Ronaldo scored a free-kick, Messi answered with one too,” no more “Messi lifted a trophy, Ronaldo lifted one as well,” no more back-and-forth magic where even their missed penalties felt like part of their rivalry.

All of it will be missed—the excitement, the hype, the goals, the broken records, the eternal rivalry. That chapter will end… and football will never feel quite the same again. 🐐 🐐
They are the Michael Jackson of Football. Even in the next 100 years, we may never witness players like them again. What they did for this game is beyond imagination—they pushed the limits, inspired billions, and became the most followed icons, surpassing every other celebrity on this planet. That’s what Ronaldo and Messi truly are.
Respect.
Hope Ronaldo will win 2026 World Cup. That's gonna be insane. Internet will explode on 19 July 2026.

comments.text:
Dembélé sûrement le plus grand ballon d'or de l'histoire.
Première nomination, une victoire.
À l'unanimité des 100 journalistes très loin devant le deuxième.
La force émotionnelle de son discours de remerciements

1. Le PSG était en reconstruction
2. Avec un effectif des plus jeune, assez inexpérimenté.

3. Voilà dans quelles conditions le leadership de OD est assumé, c'est à dire, l'esprit du sacrifice personnel pour la cause collective.

4. La route vers la finale sera un parcours du combattant avec les gros clubs à chaque tournant.

5. Beaucoup de retournements de situation, c'est à dire des remontadas. Suspense et émotions intenses au rendez-vous.

6. Une victoire en final de LDC sur un score historique de 5-0, face au tombeur du FC Barcelone.

7. Le match. Un chef d'œuvre à accrocher au Louvre. Des actions de but limpides. De l'intensité malgré une domination outrageuse.

8. Un pressing et un contrepressing de OD qui détruit la tactique de l'adversaire et change la vision du rôle de l'attaquant chez les entraîneurs.

9. Les supporters en tribune combatifs comme les joueurs sur le terrain.
Osmose entre supporters, joueurs, personnel technique et la direction.

10. Les meilleurs scores d'audience télévisuelle.

11. Ousmane est entré dans le cœur des supporters et des amateurs de foot. Ce soir-là plus encore.

comments.author: @jamestaggart2663
comments.text:
The issue with VAR is that it doesn't take movement into consideration. It snaps a moment in time. Out of context.

There are too many handballs given due to the ball touching the hand when it is completely unavoidable.

Having offside where literally 2mm can make the difference?

What happened to giving the attacker the benefit when their entire job relies on running in that direction.

The fact that sometimes there is not even daylight between the red and blue lines means the current offside rule is a joke.

VAR sucks. It needs to go.

This isn't NFL or Tennis where video reviews actually work.

It does not work for Football.

comments.author: @jackwilliams2049
comments.text:
